cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of 2D pose estimation in images. Additionally, the use of Part Affinity Fields (PAFs) and the architecture design suggest a focus on deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision research. The paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories due to the use of deep learning techniques. The multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with processing images. Finally, the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category may be relevant as the paper deals with the representation and association of body parts in images, which is a common problem in computer graphics.
